      "text": "⇒ [[Konrad Hinsen]] posted: Some of my arguments go against current trends in #OpenScience, in particular the #FAIR principles. Reusability in particular is a double-edged sword. It improves productivity, and helps finding mistakes. But it also reduces diversity of perspectives, and amplifies biases. Independent critical examination requires people who remain independent.\n\nFor a detailed discussion, see \"Open Science and Epistemic Diversity: Friends or Foes?\", by @sabinaleonelli\nhttps://doi.org/10.1017/psa.2022.45 [https://scholar.social/@khinsen/110971635155148546 post]"
